{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Forensic classification of the 17 fsck faults (store backed up: 188MB bundle + 967-ticket NDJSON export at HEAD 8c3c26f72). CLASSIFICATION (8c4f AC2): NOT version-skew — the faults persist under the current ENQUEUE_ENRICH-era binary (main 2d1524ad8, fsck shows 'ensures: 5/5 applied', no newer-than-binary WARN). They are REAL but BENIGN artifacts.\n\n13 ORPHAN_EVENT: all benign snapshot-staleness from a distributed compaction-vs-reconciler WRITE RACE — the Jira reconciler (env_id=reconciler) writes an assignee EDIT, a human/bot compaction in a different clone snapshots 3.7s-147s later without having observed that EDIT (so its source_event_uuids omits it), then the reconciler re-emits an IDENTICAL assignee EDIT after the snapshot which is what actually drives live state. Live 'rebar show' verified correct for all 13 (the orphan's effect is a redundant duplicate). DISPOSITION: retire each orphan EDIT file (.json -> .json.retired, which fsck's is_active_event() skips) — lossless, touches no status. rebar compact is a no-op here (short-circuits on existing SNAPSHOT); fsck --repair-snapshots is the corruption path (rebuilds from full log) and MUST NOT be used.\n\n4 MISSING_CREATE: all local-only phantom dirs (0 tracked files, not in HEAD, no structural references). 957d/9fa4/cf5d are empty dirs (interrupted-write residue). 110e has a .cache.json holding an epic 'Operation certificates — asymmetric + environment-attributed' — which is a DUPLICATE of the already-tracked open epic 6d0d (same title); the content is NOT lost. DISPOSITION: delete all 4 local phantom dirs.\n\nROOT-CAUSE FOLLOW-UP (separate work): the compaction-vs-reconciler race will recur; a durable fix (e.g. reconciler-aware compaction sync, or compaction refusing to snapshot within N seconds of an unobserved remote write) is out of scope for this remediation-to-zero ticket."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783786264909374001,"uuid":"935051b1-f9ce-4dff-9ec3-d57c8fcadec6"}